parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag Warning Light Illumination and Occupant Classification System (OCS) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the OCS can cause the air bag warning light to illuminate, indicating that the air bag may not deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The air bag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the light stays on constantly
the light comes on and off intermittently
the passenger seat air bag off light stays on even with an adult passenger in the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The air bag did not deploy in a crash
the driver sustained injuries
the vehicle was destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the passenger airbag sensor can lead to unexpected deactivation of the airbag, potentially causing injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag sensor randomly turns off
displaying the "Passenger Airbag Off" light
even when a passenger is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can lead to a loss of critical information, such as speed, fuel level, and warning lights, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The instrument cluster fails to function
including the speedometer
and may require replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake lights can cause accidents or collisions, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intention to stop.
symptoms: The brake lights remain on even when the lights are turned off
and may be related to a recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine stalls randomly
often when turning or stopping
and may not be replicable by mechanics.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire can cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
often in the tail light or bumper area
even when parked and turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain can cause the vehicle to be unable to start, leaving the driver stranded, and may be related to other electrical issues.
symptoms: The battery drains rapidly
even when the vehicle is turned off
and may require frequent replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the alarm and locking system can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to theft or vandalism.
symptoms: The vehicle's alarm and locking system malfunction
causing the doors to unlock or not lock
and may be related to other electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dimming of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, potentially leading to accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: The headlights dim briefly when the air conditioning is turned on
and may be related to the compressor's high voltage requirement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without warning
even when the brake pedal is engaged; the vehicle surges forward or accelerates rapidly; the engine RPM increases abnormally; the vehicle fails to slow down or respond to braking input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake pedal response can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as the vehicle may not respond to braking input or may accelerate unexpectedly.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy; the brake pedal does not respond to input; the vehicle fails to slow down or stop when the brake pedal is engaged; the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when the brake pedal is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and gearshift issues can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into reverse or other gears unexpectedly; the vehicle accelerates or decelerates rapidly; the transmission slips or hesitates; the gearshift does not engage properly.
